laboratory_examinations.findings: A large, well-circumscribed, cystic lesion in the left anterior temporal lobe.
The mass was T2/FLAIR-hyperintense and T1-hypointense, with mild peripheral enhancement, internal susceptibility-weighted imaging (SWI) hypointensity, and a small enhancing nodule.
Revealed a 1 Ã— 7 cm left middle cerebral artery (MCA) aneurysm with a surrounding area of partial thrombosis.
Revealed left temporal slowing but no epileptiform activity.
